    - **Conceptual forward preference (resolver):** When `effective_track === conceptual` and `need_class` is `missing_structure` or `gate_block`, prefer `effective_action: deepen` with structural target unless hard blocker evidence exists (`incoherence`, `contradictions_detected`, `state_hygiene_failure`, `safety_critical_ambiguity`). Execution-debt codes remain advisory on conceptual and must not force recal by default.
    - Track preference: when `queue.roadmap_next_need_prefer_track_when_sparse` is true and conceptual decomposition is sparse, set `params.roadmap_track: conceptual` in the hand-off merge only when **`queue_track_param`** is **null** (no explicit **`params.roadmap_track`** on the merged queue entry).
    - Hand-off: include a compact resolver section in the roadmap Task prompt so Layer 2 can honor the selected action/target.
    - **Conceptual `effective_target` guard:** When **`effective_track`** is **`conceptual`**, **`effective_target`** (and deepen scope in **`layer1_resolver_hints`**) must prioritize **structural** roadmap work—phase/subphase notes and **NL** completeness per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/Conceptual-Execution-Handoff-Checklist|Conceptual-Execution-Handoff-Checklist]]. **Do not** set **`effective_target`** to execution-only closure artifacts (rollup PASS, REGISTRY-CI green, HR≥93) **as the sole circled locus**; those belong in **`delta_basis`** / verbose logs only. If structural evidence is missing, prefer under-touched phase paths or explicit **Conceptual-Amendments** companion targets when post-freeze.
    - **Durable gate state:** Read Second-Brain-Config `queue.gate_state_path` (default `.technical/queue-gate-state.json`). Before finalizing resolver output, merge **`gate_streak`** for composite **`gate_key`** (includes **`effective_track`** when **`queue.gate_key_includes_track`** is true) per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/Queue-Gate-State-Spec|Queue-Gate-State-Spec]]. When `queue.deterministic_gate_script_enabled` is **true**, run `python3 <queue.deterministic_gate_script_path> report --vault-root <workspace> --project-id <resolved_id> --gate-signature <sig> --effective-track <effective_track>` (with `<sig>` from the strongest available pre-dispatch evidence below) and **prefer** script JSON for `gate_streak`, `threshold_met`, and `need_class` when `threshold_met` forces `gate_block`.
    - **Spin signal:** derive `spin_signal` per project (`flat_delta`, `same_action_class_as_prev`, `flat_delta_streak`, `suspected_spin`) using current `delta_basis` and recent continuation history. Also derive `gate_block_signal` (`gate_signature`, `gate_streak`, `blocked_track`, `pivot_to_track`, `threshold_met`) from repeated contract-gate failures **and** from `queue-gate-state.json` / script `report`. Set **`gate_block_signal.blocked_track`** to **`effective_track`** for this dispatch (not merely a default when queue omits **`params.roadmap_track`**). Build `gate_signature` from the strongest available gate evidence in this order: `failed_reason` text (`mandatory little-val` / `nested-validator`), `suppress_reason` (`post_little_val_hard_block_consumed`), validator `primary_code`, then first hard-block `reason_codes[]`.
    - **Gate-block promotion:** when `queue.gate_block_detection_enabled` is true and `gate_block_signal.gate_streak >= queue.gate_block_streak_threshold`, set resolver output to `need_class: gate_block` before follow-up synthesis. If `queue.prefer_track_shift_on_gate_block` is true and track is not explicitly user-locked, set `pivot_to_track` to the opposite track (`conceptual` <-> `execution`).
    - **Inter-comms alignment audit:** after Task return, compare outbound resolver hints with returned effective action/follow-up action and classify `resolver_alignment` as `aligned` | `partially_aligned` | `overridden_by_user_lock` | `drifted` for logging/telemetry.
