# Part B — Task-queue flow (PROCESS TASK QUEUE)

When the user said **PROCESS TASK QUEUE** (or EAT-QUEUE with intent for task queue), run this flow.

## B.1. Read queue

- Read `3-Resources/Task-Queue.md`. Parse line-by-line; skip non-JSON lines. Require `mode` (string). If no valid entries, exit and optionally append to Watcher-Result and Mobile-Pending-Actions "Task queue empty". Fast-path: exactly one valid line → go to B.2.

## B.2. Dispatch by mode

- **TASK_ROADMAP**: roadmap-ingest skill; backup and per-change snapshot before writes; Watcher-Result and Mobile-Pending-Actions.
- **TASK_COMPLETE**: task-complete-validate skill; Watcher-Result and Mobile-Pending-Actions.
- **ADD_ROADMAP_ITEM**: parse primaryPath, secondaryPath, section, insertType; duplicate check; append with append_conf ≥85%; snapshot primary before append; log and Mobile-Pending-Actions.
- **EXPAND_ROAD**: expand-road-assist; post-step Phase Direction Wrapper per Cursor-Skill-Pipelines-Reference § Phase-direction wrapper creation when applicable; log and Mobile-Pending-Actions.
- **REORDER_ROADMAP**, **DUPLICATE_ROADMAP**, **MERGE_ROADMAPS**, **EXPORT_ROADMAP**, **PROGRESS_REPORT**: per [auto-queue-processor.mdc](.cursor/rules/context/auto-queue-processor.mdc) § Dispatch by mode.
- Unknown mode → skip; append failure to Watcher-Result and Mobile-Pending-Actions.

## B.3. Log and update

- Append one line per processed entry to Watcher-Result. Always update `3-Resources/Mobile-Pending-Actions.md` with post-process status per entry.

## B.4. Banner cleanup

- If success count > failure count: for each affected note (filePath/source_file from processed entries), remove pending callouts matching `> [!note] Pending: … queued — run **PROCESS TASK QUEUE** or **EAT-QUEUE** to apply.` (or equivalent). When failures dominate, do not remove banners.

## B.5. Clear processed entries (optional)

- Per implementation choice: remove or mark processed lines in Task-Queue.md; or keep append-only and document clear step.

## Exclusions (task queue)

- Do not process entries whose filePath is under Watcher-protected paths or Backups/.

---

## Watcher-Result contract

- For both flows, append the one-line format per requestId. See [watcher-result-append.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/watcher-result-append.mdc).

## Safety

- Step 0 (prompt-queue) always runs first so approved wrappers are never stuck. Missing queue file or zero valid entries → exit without dispatch after Step 0. Missing source_file or unknown mode → skip entry, log failure, continue. queue_failed entries are never processed; only written back when they fail again. All destructive work is in downstream pipelines/skills; this subagent only orchestrates.
